songs.title: Hysterical

album.full_title: Turtle Tales From Overseas by Pamela Hute
album.name: Turtle Tales From Overseas

songs.lyrics:
I can fly and see you over here
Let the things around and come and fear
I dont know who I am and what I am
I cant feel the pain on my hands
I broke, love is hysterical
In this lazy home
Youre on my mind
Red coke, rock is hysterical
In their lazy rooms
Whats on their minds?
I should die and love you over here
Let those sins away and come with fear
I dont care who I am and what I am
I wont feel your pain on my hands

Bring me back love

songs.title: Pink Safari

album.full_title: Turtle Tales From Overseas by Pamela Hute
album.name: Turtle Tales From Overseas

songs.lyrics:
In the hotel room she lies alone
She waits for all the things
She asked him to bring to life
In the metal case
Theres nothing left
Except a ring, a god damn ring
She hates to wear
Pink safari
She waits for all the words
She asked him to bring to her
In the wooden box
Theres nothing left
Except a pearl, a god damn pearl
She hates to see
Pink safari
In the hotel room
She cries alone
In the metal box
Theres nothing left
Except a ring, a god damn ring
She hates to wear
Pink safari

songs.lyrics:
Oh you felt some options fall just from the sky

Its not like I thought

Taste it

Its not like you said
Its not like you thought
All your loneliness stuck inside your bones
Its not like you thought
Its not like I thought

songs.lyrics:

There is only one way
Ive got to be you

How many of you

Tell me what you do
Friend
Im changing my ways
Im changing my aim
Im changing it all now
Dear, Ive got to be a fool
Oh, thats the only way
Regardless of what you say
Regardless of what you meant

songs.title: Chocolate Soup

album.full_title: Turtle Tales From Overseas by Pamela Hute
album.name: Turtle Tales From Overseas

songs.lyrics:
Need some time to eat my chocolate soup
Close the door and watch the rocket land
Yeah watch the rocket land
I am there I can't hear a sound
Where are you?
Are we tomorrow ? I don't care
Let me feel the dark space
See the stars
I don't want a rocket no more
I don't need no time
I do need some stars
